<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-80-0468 </DOCNO><TEXT>The oil consumption of OECD in 1987 was 35,700,000 barrels/day which wasabout 1.5 % larger than that of 1986. The growth of about 1 % is expectedfor 1988. The OPEC's production of crude oil in January is temporarilyestimated as 17 million barrels/day. Little change was observed in OECDin the private stock in the 4th quarter of 1987. Prices of most of thecrude oil and products went down in the period between the end of Januaryand the end of February. In many of the OECD coutries, the cost of crudeoil is now about 60 - 70 % of that in the middle of 1985. Summarizedreports are made on oil consumption, supply, balance of supply and demand,and price. Recent price trends of imported crude oil and final demandproducts in the U.S., Japan, and Germany are introduced. (4 figs, 12tabs)</TEXT></DOC>